The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for the detection and ranging of marine vessels using passive sonar data. This involves signal processing, machine learning, and sensor networks, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of CNNs for classification and detection tasks falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
